---
// Editorial split — 17:10 horizontal photo on the left, narrative on the
// right. Modeled on Black Tomato's "What we do" / "Pursuit of Feeling"
// alternating split-image sections. The aspect-ratio break from the
// portrait Picker cards above is what gives the page its magazine
// rhythm.
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
---

<section class="bg-bone text-primary py-24 sm:py-32 lg:py-40 border-t border-rule">
  <div class="max-w-[1400px] mx-auto px-7 lg:px-14">
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-12 gap-10 lg:gap-16 items-center">
      <div class="lg:col-span-7 order-2 lg:order-1">
        <figure class="relative aspect-[17/10] overflow-hidden bg-primary/5">
          <img
            src="/img/source/hero/04-cockpit-sunrise.jpg"
            alt="Coffee on the cockpit bench of a catamaran as the sun comes up over the anchorage"
            loading="lazy"
            decoding="async"
            class="absolute inset-0 w-full h-full object-cover"
          />
        </figure>
        <figcaption class="font-label-caps uppercase tracking-[0.22em] text-[0.5625rem] font-semibold text-primary/45 mt-3">
          Plate 01 · Sunrise · Cooper Island, BVI
        </figcaption>
      </div>

      <div class="lg:col-span-5 order-1 lg:order-2">
        <p class="font-label-caps uppercase tracking-[0.28em] text-[0.625rem] font-semibold text-primary/70 mb-5">
          The rhythm of a week
        </p>
        <h2
          class="font-display font-light leading-[1.05] tracking-[-0.025em] text-balance"
          style="font-size: clamp(1.875rem, 3.5vw + 1rem, 2.75rem); font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 96, 'SOFT' 30, 'WONK' 0;"
        >
          You wake to coffee on deck, and the rest
          <span class="italic" style="font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 96, 'SOFT' 60, 'WONK' 1;">
            writes itself.
          </span>
        </h2>
        <div class="mt-8 space-y-5 font-body-lg text-[1.0625rem] leading-[1.7] text-primary/75 text-balance">
          <p>
            Most days: a short, easy passage between anchorages by mid-morning,
            a long open afternoon to swim and read, dinner aboard or ashore
            depending on the cove. You're never on the boat for more than four
            hours at a stretch.
          </p>
          <p>
            What gets removed is the planning. Clint sets the route the night
            before based on weather and group mood. Dodie shops the markets we
            pass. You wake up, the day is set up.
          </p>
        </div>
        <a
          href="/aboard"
          class="group inline-flex items-center gap-3 mt-9 font-label-caps uppercase tracking-[0.22em] text-[0.75rem] font-semibold text-primary border-b-2 border-accent pb-1 hover:text-accent transition-colors"
        >
          What's aboard
          <svg viewBox="0 0 16 16" class="size-3 group-hover:translate-x-1 transition-transform" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" aria-hidden="true">
            <path d="M1 8h13M9 3l5 5-5 5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" />
          </svg>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
